    "name": "Ashley Wahid Hasyim Jakarta",
    "detail": "We had a Deluxe Twin room and it looked bigger than 22 sq.m. Maybe because of the very good space utilization. The bath room is big too, with a large wash basin countertop to put all our cosmetics and toiletries. Room was very clean and smells good. Aircon was extremely silent and effective. Bed linens and bath towels were immaculately white. Breakfast was very good with main dishes changing everyday. We particularly liked the nasi goreng and all the beef and chicken dishes. For a not so large hotel, the three elevators were luxury. No waiting to go up or down the room. Transportation out of the hotel was very convenient as there was always a Bluebird taxi waiting in the hotel driveway. Best of all, the room price was very reasonable, probably the lowest price among the many hotels along Wahid Hasyim Road. Really great value for money. We had a wonderful vacation in Jakarta and a better part of it was staying at Ashley Hotel with its friendly front desk staff. ",
